You are given a m x n 2D integer array grid and an integer k. You start at the top-left cell (0, 0) and your goal is to reach the bottom‐right cell (m - 1, n - 1).

There are two types of moves available:

Normal move: You can move right or down from your current cell (i, j), i.e. you can move to (i, j + 1) (right) or (i + 1, j) (down). The cost is the value of the destination cell.

Teleportation: You can teleport from any cell (i, j), to any cell (x, y) such that grid[x][y] <= grid[i][j]; the cost of this move is 0. You may teleport at most k times.

Return the minimum total cost to reach cell (m - 1, n - 1) from (0, 0).

 

Example 1:

Input: grid = [[1,3,3],[2,5,4],[4,3,5]], k = 2

Output: 7

Explanation:

Initially we are at (0, 0) and cost is 0.

Current Position	Move	New Position	Total Cost
(0, 0)	Move Down	(1, 0)	0 + 2 = 2
(1, 0)	Move Right	(1, 1)	2 + 5 = 7
(1, 1)	Teleport to (2, 2)	(2, 2)	7 + 0 = 7
The minimum cost to reach bottom-right cell is 7.

Example 2:

Input: grid = [[1,2],[2,3],[3,4]], k = 1

Output: 9

Explanation:

Initially we are at (0, 0) and cost is 0.

Current Position	Move	New Position	Total Cost
(0, 0)	Move Down	(1, 0)	0 + 2 = 2
(1, 0)	Move Right	(1, 1)	2 + 3 = 5
(1, 1)	Move Down	(2, 1)	5 + 4 = 9
The minimum cost to reach bottom-right cell is 9.

 

Constraints:

2 <= m, n <= 80
m == grid.length
n == grid[i].length
0 <= grid[i][j] <= 104
0 <= k <= 10
-----------------------------------------


class Solution {
    public int minCost(int[][] grid, int k) {
        int m = grid.length, n = grid[0].length;
        
        // Step 1: Create list of all grid points for sorting
        List<int[]> points = new ArrayList<>();
        for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
                points.add(new int[] { i, j });
            }
        }
        // Sort by cell value ascending → enables downward cost propagation
        points.sort(Comparator.comparingInt(p -> grid[p[0]][p[1]]));
        
        // Step 2: Initialize cost matrix (min cost from cell to destination)
        int[][] costs = new int[m][n];
        for (int[] row : costs) Arrays.fill(row, Integer.MAX_VALUE);
        
        // Step 3: Process k+1 layers (0 to k teleports used)
        for (int t = 0; t <= k; t++) {
            // ===== PHASE 1: VALUE-BASED TELEPORT PROPAGATION =====
            int minCost = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
            // j marks start of current value group; i scans forward
            for (int i = 0, j = 0; i < points.size(); i++) {
                // Track minimum cost seen in all cells with value ≤ current
                int[] p = points.get(i);
                minCost = Math.min(minCost, costs[p[0]][p[1]]);
                
                // Skip within same-value groups (don't propagate prematurely)
                if (i + 1 < points.size() && 
                    grid[p[0]][p[1]] == grid[points.get(i+1)[0]][points.get(i+1)[1]]) {
                    continue;
                }
                
                // Assign minCost to ENTIRE group of equal-valued cells
                // Why group? Teleportation works for ALL cells with value ≤ V simultaneously
                for (int r = j; r <= i; r++) {
                    int[] q = points.get(r);
                    costs[q[0]][q[1]] = minCost;
                }
                j = i + 1; // Start new group
            }
            
            // ===== PHASE 2: NORMAL MOVE PROPAGATION (DP) =====
            // Process bottom→top, right→left to ensure dependencies resolved
            for (int i = m - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
                for (int j = n - 1; j >= 0; j--) {
                    // Destination base case
                    if (i == m - 1 && j == n - 1) {
                        costs[i][j] = 0;
                        continue;
                    }
                    
                    // Move down: from (i,j) to (i+1,j) costs grid[i+1][j]
                    if (i != m - 1) {
                        costs[i][j] = Math.min(
                            costs[i][j],
                            costs[i + 1][j] + grid[i + 1][j]
                        );
                    }
                    // Move right: from (i,j) to (i,j+1) costs grid[i][j+1]
                    if (j != n - 1) {
                        costs[i][j] = Math.min(
                            costs[i][j],
                            costs[i][j + 1] + grid[i][j + 1]
                        );
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        return costs[0][0];
    }
}
